Prestigious Healer		KEY:Trait ~ Prestigious Healer					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait					PREMULT:1,[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait],[PREVAREQ:BypassTraitRestriction,1],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Trait ~ Prestigious Healer]																PREREGION:Cheliax						DESC:Once per day as an immediate action when you cast a spell of the healing subschool, you can attempt a Diplomacy check to improve the attitude of your target or anyone within 30 feet who can see you before the end of your next turn. You gain a +2 trait bonus on this check.																																																																															SOURCEPAGE:p.2
Heir of Chu Ye			KEY:Trait ~ Heir of Chu Ye			NAMEISPI:YES	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait					PREMULT:1,[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait],[PREVAREQ:BypassTraitRestriction,1],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Trait ~ Heir of Chu Ye]																PREREGION:Tian Xia					DESC:If you would take a penalty for using the Heal skill to treat deadly wounds without one or more uses of a healer's kit, that penalty is reduced by 2 (minimum no penalty). Additionally, a creature can benefit from you treating its deadly wounds if you do so within 48 hours of its injury instead of within 24 hours.																																																																								SOURCEPAGE:p.3
Iobarian Survivor			KEY:Trait ~ Iobarian Survivor			NAMEISPI:YES	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait					PREMULT:1,[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait],[PREVAREQ:BypassTraitRestriction,1],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Trait ~ Iobarian Survivor]																PREREGION:Iobaria						DESC:Whenever you are exposed to a disease while you are trying to treat an afflicted creature, you gain a +4 trait bonus on your Fortitude saving throw to resist contracting the disease yourself.																																																																																													SOURCEPAGE:p.3
Jadwiga Medicine			KEY:Trait ~ Jadwiga Medicine			NAMEISPI:YES	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait					PREMULT:1,[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait],[PREVAREQ:BypassTraitRestriction,1],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Trait ~ Jadwiga Medicine]																PREREGION:Irrisen						DESC:Once per day as an immediate action when you cast a spell of the healing subschool or a hex that produces the effect of such a spell, you can attempt an Intimidate check to demoralize your target or anyone who can see you within 30 feet. You gain a +2 trait bonus on this check.																																																																														SOURCEPAGE:p.3
Curse Queller			KEY:Trait ~ Curse Queller						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait					PREMULT:1,[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait],[PREVAREQ:BypassTraitRestriction,1],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Trait ~ Curse Queller]																	PREREGION:Osirion						DESC:Whenever a caster level check is required to treat an affliction with magic (such as when casting remove curse on a cursed creature or object), you gain a +2 trait bonus on your caster level check. Additionally, you gain a +1 trait bonus on your saving throws against curses.																																																																															SOURCEPAGE:p.3	ASPECT:SaveBonus|+1 circumstance to saving throws vs. curses
Educated Druggist			KEY:Trait ~ Educated Druggist						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait					PREMULT:1,[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait],[PREVAREQ:BypassTraitRestriction,1],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Trait ~ Educated Druggist]	PREMULT:1,[PREREGION:Osibu],[PREREGION:Thuvia],[PREREGION:Tian Xia],[PREREGION:Ustalav]									DESC:Any alchemical remedies you administer that provide an alchemical bonus have that bonus increased by 1. These remedies also restore 1 hit point to the target in addition to their usual effects.																																																																																												SOURCEPAGE:p.10
Mana Wastes Medic			KEY:Trait ~ Mana Wastes Medic			NAMEISPI:YES	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait					PREMULT:1,[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait],[PREVAREQ:BypassTraitRestriction,1],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Trait ~ Mana Wastes Medic]																PREREGION:Mana Wastes		DESCISPI:YES	DESC:After witnessing a terrible disaster result from an attempt at magical healing in the Mana Wastes, you are careful and methodical when crafting your own healing tinctures. The amount of hit points restored by your Heal checks to treat deadly wounds and your extracts of the healing subschool is increased by 1.																																																																									SOURCEPAGE:p.10
Skilled Surgeon			KEY:Trait ~ Skilled Surgeon						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait					PREMULT:1,[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait],[PREVAREQ:BypassTraitRestriction,1],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Trait ~ Skilled Surgeon]	PREMULT:1,[PREREGION:Qadira],[PREREGION:Ustalav]															DESC:Whenever you perform surgery or otherwise must deal damage to remove a condition or affliction, you roll the damage but use the minimum result unless you rolled the maximum result. The amount of hit points or points of ability damage restored each day when you provide long-term care is increased by 1.																																																																										SOURCEPAGE:p.10
Near-Death Experience		KEY:Trait ~ Near-Death Experience					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait					PREMULT:1,[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait],[PREVAREQ:BypassTraitRestriction,1],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Trait ~ Near-Death Experience]															PREREGION:Belkzen			DESCISPI:YES	DESC:You had a close brush with death that you survived only thanks to one of the witch doctors of Belkzen, and your body has learned to cling to life in dire situations. You gain a +1 trait bonus on Constitution checks to stabilize, and you don't die until your hit points drop to a negative amount equal to 2 + your Constitution score.																																																																					SOURCEPAGE:p.16
Debt to a Witch			KEY:Trait ~ Debt to a Witch						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait					PREMULT:1,[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait],[PREVAREQ:BypassTraitRestriction,1],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Trait ~ Debt to a Witch]																PREREGION:Irrisen						DESC:Your life was spared in youth by the magic of a White Witch healer who was using your survival to perpetuate her agenda. Her magic was painful, but it made your body stronger. You gain a +2 trait bonus on saving throws against spells with the cold descriptor and against the dangers of cold weather.																																																																											SOURCEPAGE:p.16	ASPECT:SaveBonus|+2 trait bonus to saving throws vs. cold
Patron's Boon			KEY:Trait ~ Patron's Boon						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait					PREMULT:1,[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait],[PREVAREQ:BypassTraitRestriction,1],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Trait ~ Patron's Boon]																	PREREGION:Rahadoum		DESCISPI:YES	DESC:In your youth, a Rahadoumi witch granted you a boon promoting your continued health and long life. The DCs of any Heal checks to stop bleed damage you are suffering are reduced by 4.																																																																																														SOURCEPAGE:p.16
Godless Resolve			KEY:Trait ~ Godless Resolve						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait					PREMULT:1,[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait],[PREVAREQ:BypassTraitRestriction,1],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Trait ~ Godless Resolve]	PREMULT:1,[PREREGION:Bachuan],[PREREGION:Rahadoum],[PREREGION:Touvette]												DESC:Some brilliant and earnest speech or other performance inspired you to take charge of your own health rather than begging indifferent or outlawed deities for deliverance. Heal is a class skill for you, and you gain a +2 trait bonus on Heal checks to stabilize dying creatures and stop bleeding.																																																																										CSKILL:Heal	SOURCEPAGE:p.18	ASPECT:SkillBonus|+2 trait bonus on Heal checks to stabilize
Sustaining Performance		KEY:Trait ~ Sustaining Performance					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait					PREMULT:1,[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait],[PREVAREQ:BypassTraitRestriction,1],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Trait ~ Sustaining Performance]															PREREGION:The Shackles					DESC:Abandoned by a traditional healer at a critical time, you improvised a tale or jokes to keep up the spirits of someone in dire health. Once per day as a standard action, you can attempt a DC 15 Perform check with an audible component (such as comedy, oratory, sing, or with any instrument) to stabilize a dying creature that can hear you within 30 feet. You can also attempt Perform checks instead of Heal checks to provide long-term care.																																																			SOURCEPAGE:p.18
Animal-Spirit Vitality		KEY:Trait ~ Animal-Spirit Vitality					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait					PREMULT:1,[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait],[PREVAREQ:BypassTraitRestriction,1],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Trait ~ Animal-Spirit Vitality]															PREREGION:Kyonin			DESCISPI:YES	DESC:The elven druids of Kyonin taught you to commune with the natural healing powers of animals. Once per day when you cast a spell that restores hit points, you restore 1 additional hit point for every die rolled as long as a creature of the animal type is within 50 feet. You must decide to use this ability before rolling to determine the number of hit points that your spell restores.																																																													SOURCEPAGE:p.22
Guerrilla Mender			KEY:Trait ~ Guerrilla Mender						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait					PREMULT:1,[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait],[PREVAREQ:BypassTraitRestriction,1],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Trait ~ Guerrilla Mender]																PREREGION:Nirmathas		DESCISPI:YES	DESC:With the help of a druidic healer, you narrowly escaped death by disease or poisoning while on the run from Molthuni militias, whether contracting the ailment was an accident or you were the victim of more sinister forces. Whenever you successfully use the Heal skill to treat an ally's poison or disease, you grant the ally an additional +1 trait bonus on the saving throw against the disease or poison. Heal is a class skill for you.																																																		CSKILL:Heal	SOURCEPAGE:p.22
Mwangi Herbal Tradition		KEY:Trait ~ Mwangi Herbal Tradition		NAMEISPI:YES	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait					PREMULT:1,[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait],[PREVAREQ:BypassTraitRestriction,1],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Trait ~ Mwangi Herbal Tradition]															PREREGION:Mwangi Expanse	DESCISPI:YES	DESC:You are trained in a Mwangi tradition of herbalism dating back to the Age of Darkness and therefore have great insight into how to use the natural ingredients at your disposal to nurse an ailing body. You gain a +4 trait bonus on Heal checks when providing long-term care, and Heal is a class skill for you.																																																																							CSKILL:Heal	SOURCEPAGE:p.22
Servitor of Spirits		KEY:Trait ~ Servitor of Spirits					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait					PREMULT:1,[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait],[PREVAREQ:BypassTraitRestriction,1],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Trait ~ Servitor of Spirits]																PREREGION:Tian Xia					DESC:For as long as you can remember, the spirits have always whispered into your ears and guided you-provided that you appease them. At the start of each day, you can choose one medium spirit (Pathfinder RPG Occult Adventures 33-36) and accept one of its taboos for 24 hours. As long as you don't break that taboo, once during the next 24 hours, you can add a +1 trait bonus to any one roll, check, or saving throw (but not to AC) listed under your chosen spirit's spirit bonus. Using this ability is a free action that you can use even if it isn't your turn. If you are a medium, the spirit you choose with this trait must be the same as the spirit you are channeling and vice versa.											SOURCEPAGE:p.27

#Religion Traits

Bloody Vengeance			KEY:Trait ~ Bloody Vengeance						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.ReligionTrait	PREDEITY:1,Vildeis	PREMULT:1,[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.ReligionTrait],[PREVAREQ:BypassTraitRestriction,1],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Trait ~ Bloody Vengeance]																					DESCISPI:YES	DESC:You were slain by evil forces as a child, but a follower of Vildeis restored you to life. Now you live on in service to the Cardinal Martyr, battling the forces of evil so no other child will know the icy grip of death. You gain a +2 trait bonus on attack rolls to confirm critical hits against any creature that has at least a faint evil aura (see detect evil).																																																																SOURCEPAGE:p.12
Envoy of Healing			KEY:Trait ~ Envoy of Healing						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.ReligionTrait	PREDEITY:1,Sarenrae	PREMULT:1,[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.ReligionTrait],[PREVAREQ:BypassTraitRestriction,1],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Trait ~ Envoy of Healing]																					DESCISPI:YES	DESC:You strive to spread the Dawnflower's message of kindness and compassion throughout the land, no matter how dangerous the road may be. Whenever you use channel energy, fervor, or lay on hands to heal a living creature, you can reroll any healing die roll that results in a natural 1 (you must use the new result).																																																																								SOURCEPAGE:p.12
Scarred by War			KEY:Trait ~ Scarred by War						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.ReligionTrait	PREDEITY:1,Dalenydra	PREMULT:1,[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.ReligionTrait],[PREVAREQ:BypassTraitRestriction,1],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Trait ~ Scarred by War]																					DESCISPI:YES	DESC:You have experienced firsthand the horrors of war, which have left you physically or mentally scarred. Now you have committed yourself to the teachings of the Blessed Attendant, seeking to heal those wounded in combat and to prevent battles from occurring whenever you can. You gain a +1 trait bonus on Diplomacy checks outside of combat. In addition, when you heal creatures other than yourself using class abilities, feats, spells, and spell-completion or spell-trigger magic items, you restore 1 additional hit point.																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.12


